## Realtime Priority Stress Benchmark

```elixir
priority_form =
  Kino.Control.form(
    [
      probe_samples: Kino.Input.number("Realtime probes", default: 200),
      reliable_workers: Kino.Input.number("Reliable workers", default: 4),
      reliable_flood_ms: Kino.Input.number("Flood duration (ms)", default: 5_000),
      realtime_deadline_us: Kino.Input.number("Realtime deadline (us)", default: max(config.cycle_ms * 2_000, 5_000))
    ],
    submit: "Run priority stress benchmark"
  )

Kino.render(priority_form)
```

```elixir
priority_frame = Kino.Frame.new()

Kino.render(priority_frame)
Kino.Frame.render(priority_frame, Kino.Markdown.new("Submit the form to stress realtime priority against reliable flooding."))

Kino.listen(priority_form, fn %{data: priority} ->
  current_config = :persistent_term.get(:ethercat_hardware_validation_config)

  result =
    Example.Hardware.priority_stress(
      current_config,
      priority.probe_samples,
      priority.reliable_workers,
      priority.reliable_flood_ms,
      priority.realtime_deadline_us
    )

  Kino.Frame.render(priority_frame, Kino.Tree.new(result))
end)

:ok
```

## Wait for DC Lock

```elixir
dc_wait_form =
  Kino.Control.form(
    [
      timeout_ms: Kino.Input.number("Timeout (ms)", default: 5_000)
    ],
    submit: "Wait for DC lock"
  )

Kino.render(dc_wait_form)
```

```elixir
dc_wait_frame = Kino.Frame.new()

Kino.render(dc_wait_frame)
Kino.Frame.render(dc_wait_frame, Kino.Markdown.new("Submit the form to wait for DC lock and refresh DC status."))

Kino.listen(dc_wait_form, fn %{data: dc_wait} ->
  result = %{
    wait_result: EtherCAT.await_dc_locked(dc_wait.timeout_ms),
    dc_status: EtherCAT.dc_status(),
    reference_clock: EtherCAT.reference_clock()
  }

  Kino.Frame.render(dc_wait_frame, Kino.Tree.new(result))
end)

:ok
```

## Quick Checklist

- `runtime snapshot` should show `phase: :operational`
- `manual single-channel write` should echo the written bit on the matching input
- `manual full-mask write` should converge to the requested mask without timeouts
- `single-channel latency` should be stable and close to one or two domain cycles
- `full-width loopback` should show zero or near-zero timeouts under steady load
- `priority stress` should keep realtime probe latencies bounded while reliable dispatch increases
- `wait for DC lock` should eventually return `:ok` when DC is enabled and the topology supports it
